went anywhere.

67
00:04:11,555 --> 00:04:14,079
The ranch, the mustangs,
it's all he cared about

68
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:16,125
more than anything.

69
00:04:16,299 --> 00:04:17,735
- And?

70
00:04:17,909 --> 00:04:19,433
- So eventually I met your mom,

71
00:04:19,607 --> 00:04:21,348
and she wanted to move
to Los Angeles.

72
00:04:21,522 --> 00:04:23,611
I wanted to get out.

73
00:04:23,785 --> 00:04:25,395
My dad said if
you leave this ranch,

74
00:04:25,569 --> 00:04:27,136
don't bother coming back,
and don't bother calling.

75
00:04:27,310 --> 00:04:29,791
- So...
- So, I didn't call.

76
00:04:29,965 --> 00:04:32,533
- Neither did he?
- Stubborn as a mule.

77
00:04:32,707 --> 00:04:35,840
- Mom said you're just like him.

78
00:04:36,014 --> 00:04:38,278
- Oh yeah?
What else did she say?

79
00:04:38,452 --> 00:04:40,062
- She said you loved him.

80
00:04:40,236 --> 00:04:41,411
- She said that?

81
00:04:41,585 --> 00:04:43,283
- Mm-hmm.

82
00:04:57,514 --> 00:04:58,776
So where's main street?

83
00:04:58,950 --> 00:05:00,082
- This is the main street.

84
00:05:00,256 --> 00:05:01,388
- This is a ghost town.

85
00:05:01,562 --> 00:05:04,304
- Hey! Sam!
[Honks horn]

86
00:05:08,351 --> 00:05:10,658
- Bobby hart.
