- Well, he's inside getting the
grand tour from the hillbilly.

145
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:43,941
- Timmy!
- Ah, hey, grandpa.

146
00:07:44,115 --> 00:07:46,117
- [Laughs]
Tim.

147
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:48,816
I want you to meet
our interim sheriff.

148
00:07:48,990 --> 00:07:50,644
So you just better quit
that shoplifting, you hear?

149
00:07:50,818 --> 00:07:52,167
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

150
00:07:52,341 --> 00:07:53,777
- Vicky's boy, from Fresno.

151
00:07:53,951 --> 00:07:55,953
Staying the summer
with us old farts.

152
00:07:56,127 --> 00:07:57,999
- Uh-huh. Arliss, I'm gonna
need a couple of days

153
00:07:58,173 --> 00:07:59,479
to get settled.

154
00:07:59,653 --> 00:08:00,915
So, why don't I come back
on Monday?

155
00:08:01,089 --> 00:08:03,178
- Take all the time you need.
[Laughs]

156
00:08:03,352 --> 00:08:05,354
No crime here.
No, sir.

157
00:08:05,528 --> 00:08:07,487
- Take care.
Come on, honey.

158
00:08:12,143 --> 00:08:13,057
[Car door opens]

159
00:08:26,157 --> 00:08:28,420
- What do you think, honey?
- This looks...

160
00:08:28,595 --> 00:08:30,292
Just like an old western movie.

161
00:08:42,217 --> 00:08:44,915
[Horse neighs]

162
00:08:45,089 --> 00:08:46,613
- Hey.

163
00:08:46,787 --> 00:08:48,179
- Howdy, Bob.
- How are you doing?

164
00:08:48,353 --> 00:08:50,225
- Good.

165
00:08:50,399 --> 00:08:52,880
Hey, girl.
Wow.

166
00:08:53,054 --> 00:08:55,622
I haven't seen you
since you were a toddler.

167
00:08:55,796 --> 00:09:00,670
I bet your daddy's got a grin
from ear to ear on his face.

168
00:09:00,844 --> 00:09:01,802
- About time he smiled
at something I did.

169
00:09:01,976 --> 00:09:03,543
- You'd be surprised, Bob.

170
00:09:05,414 --> 00:09:06,763
Well, what do you think?
You want to go see him?

171
00:09:06,937 --> 00:09:08,025
- Oh, you bet.
- See what?

172
00:09:08,199 --> 00:09:09,810
- I'll show you.

