about six months ago

177
00:09:37,228 --> 00:09:39,013
pretty little Philly
named Lucinda.

178
00:09:39,187 --> 00:09:40,710
- Lucinda?

179
00:09:40,884 --> 00:09:42,233
- Yeah, it's my mother's name.

180
00:09:42,407 --> 00:09:43,844
The little one there,

181
00:09:44,018 --> 00:09:46,455
the runt,
the name's Bob.

182
00:09:46,629 --> 00:09:49,589
Your granddad chose that one.

183
00:09:49,763 --> 00:09:51,591
- So where's Lucinda?

184
00:09:51,765 --> 00:09:56,639
- Lucinda's back at the barn.
Her mother died of some disease.

185
00:09:56,813 --> 00:09:58,772
She's got no mom
to suckle.

186
00:09:58,946 --> 00:10:01,513
Herd's turned her out,
and she won't eat.

187
00:10:01,688 --> 00:10:03,820
We're doing whatever we can
to keep her going.

188
00:10:03,994 --> 00:10:06,693
The vet's keeping an eye
on her.

189
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:08,085
- Is it still old pain in the...
- hey.

190
00:10:08,259 --> 00:10:10,044
You're gonna like this one.

191
00:10:10,218 --> 00:10:13,177
[Horses whinny in the distance]

192
00:10:13,351 --> 00:10:16,833
- I thought you said you could
set your watch by this vet.

193
00:10:17,007 --> 00:10:18,269
- I did.

194
00:10:18,443 --> 00:10:20,707
[Horse snorts]

195
00:10:20,881 --> 00:10:25,276
- Wait a minute.
Is that the vet?

196
00:10:27,017 --> 00:10:28,062
- Yeah.

197
00:10:28,236 --> 00:10:29,716
- Hey, Hank.

198
00:10:29,890 --> 00:10:31,239
How's your baby Lucinda?

199
00:10:31,413 --> 00:10:32,980
- Well, you tell me.

200
00:10:33,154 --> 00:10:35,069
Better yet, tell him.
He's the new owner.

201
00:10:35,243 --> 00:10:38,115
- Robert hart,
the prodigal son.

202
00:10:38,289 --> 00:10:39,943
- [Laughs]
- Emily Benson.

203
00:10:40,117 --> 00:10:41,771
Took over pain in the butt's
practice three years ago.

204
00:10:41,945 --> 00:10:43,164
- Good.

205
00:10:43,338 --> 00:10:44,556
- Your father was
a real charmer.

206
00:10:44,731 --> 00:10:47,342
- He was?
- Oh, yeah. I loved him.

207
00:10:47,516 --> 00:10:48,386
[Horse snorts]
- Well, that's nice.

208
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:51,520
- This must be Madison.

209
00:10:51,694 --> 00:10:53,522
Your nose is
the talk of the town.

210
00:10:53,696 --> 00:10:57,091
- Yeah, well, what can I say.
Big nose, small town.

211
00:10:57,265 --> 00:10:58,222
[Horse sniffs]

212
00:11:00,268 --> 00:11:02,096
- Want to hear something?
Come here.

213
00:11:02,270 --> 00:11:04,664
Come here.

214
00:11:12,715 --> 00:11:16,414
Ok, just hold that right there.

215
00:11:18,547 --> 00:11:20,157
- Is there any improvement?

216
00:11:20,331 --> 00:11:21,898
- She's still not
eating much, is she?

217
00:11:22,072 --> 00:11:23,857
- What are we gonna do?

218
00:11:24,031 --> 00:11:25,685
I don't even want to think
about putting her down.

219
00:11:27,556 --> 00:11:28,557
- I don't think so.

220
00:11:30,820 --> 00:11:32,343
You gave her
your grandma's name.

221
00:11:32,517 --> 00:11:34,781
If she deserves a name,
she deserves a chance.

222
00:11:34,955 --> 00:11:36,521
- The doctor will know
what to do, Madison.

223
00:11:38,349 --> 00:11:41,265
- Oh, look, let's just
try to get her to eat, ok.

224
00:11:41,439 --> 00:11:44,791
We'll keep a watch on her
for the next few days, ok?

225
00:11:44,965 --> 00:11:47,402
All right, sorry.
I got to get going.

226
00:11:47,576 --> 00:11:50,057
I've got a...
Got a goat with a cold.

227
00:11:50,231 --> 00:11:52,146
Nice to meet you guys.

228
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,451
- Bye-bye.

229
00:11:56,585 --> 00:11:58,805
- Is that Cody McMichael?

230
00:11:58,979 --> 00:12:01,590
