232
00:12:16,387 --> 00:12:17,737
Well, lovely doctor B.

233
00:12:21,610 --> 00:12:24,308
The young miss hart.

234
00:12:24,482 --> 00:12:27,181
My good old buddy Hank.
- Cody.

235
00:12:27,355 --> 00:12:30,358
- And Bobby.

236
00:12:30,532 --> 00:12:34,101
Yeah. The new sheriff.

237
00:12:34,275 --> 00:12:36,190
Congratulations.

238
00:12:36,364 --> 00:12:38,627
Man, you're the last person
I ever figured

239
00:12:38,801 --> 00:12:39,802
would be back here in hope.

240
00:12:39,976 --> 00:12:40,803
- [Laughs]

241
00:12:40,977 --> 00:12:42,457
- So, how you doing?

242
00:12:42,631 --> 00:12:44,633
- I'm doing just fine, Cody.
How about you?

243
00:12:44,807 --> 00:12:46,417
- Pretty darn near terrific.

244
00:12:46,591 --> 00:12:47,854
Building that mall in town.

245
00:12:48,028 --> 00:12:50,639
- What brings you up here?
- Hey.

246
00:12:50,813 --> 00:12:52,815
Just being neighborly.

247
00:12:52,989 --> 00:12:54,861
Your dad and I went
to school together

248
00:12:55,035 --> 00:12:58,429
when he was the runt and I was
captain of the football team.

249
00:12:58,603 --> 00:13:00,344
- [Laughs]
That's right.

250
00:13:00,518 --> 00:13:03,260
- [Laughs]
Yeah, I made his life miserable.

251
00:13:03,434 --> 00:13:05,959
Kids, huh?

252
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:11,355
Now, your old man,
he loved these mustangs.

