01:00:53,084 --> 01:00:54,346
- my people have put up
a lot of money

1021
01:00:54,520 --> 01:00:55,826
to get things moving.

1022
01:00:56,000 --> 01:00:59,873
This land deal is
important for all of us.

1023
01:01:00,047 --> 01:01:02,223
You realize what kind of
pressure I'm under here?

1024
01:01:02,397 --> 01:01:05,270
Now he's off making
all sorts of phone calls?

1025
01:01:05,444 --> 01:01:09,535
- And finding lighters.

1026
01:01:09,709 --> 01:01:11,580
- [Laughs]

1027
01:01:11,755 --> 01:01:14,540
- Cody,

1028
01:01:14,714 --> 01:01:16,411
did you do what I think you did?

1029
01:01:16,585 --> 01:01:18,544
- Don't think so much, arliss.

1030
01:01:18,718 --> 01:01:20,285
You just make this go away,

1031
01:01:20,459 --> 01:01:22,330
or I will.

1032
01:01:22,504 --> 01:01:23,418
- What do you mean?

1033
01:01:23,592 --> 01:01:25,377
[Cell phone ringtone]

1034
01:01:25,551 --> 01:01:27,074
Oh, hold on just a minute.

1035
01:01:29,511 --> 01:01:31,165
Hello, it's arliss.

1036
01:01:31,339 --> 01:01:32,601
- Mayor, you are going
to make the meeting, aren't you?

1037
01:01:32,776 --> 01:01:35,039
- Oh, of course.
[Laughs] Yes.

1038
01:01:35,213 --> 01:01:37,345
- It started ten minutes ago.
- I'll come right over.

1039
01:01:37,519 --> 01:01:39,217
- All right.
All the parties are here.

1040
01:01:39,391 --> 01:01:40,914
- Well, I'll leave right now.
Yes.

1041
01:01:41,088 --> 01:01:43,177
- See you in just a little bit.
- Alrighty, bye.

1042
01:01:43,351 --> 01:01:45,614
Why can't people solve
their own blasted problems?

1043
01:01:45,789 --> 01:01:47,486
- You're not going, are you?
- Hey...

1044
01:01:47,660 --> 01:01:49,096
Election's right around
the corner.

1045
01:01:50,924 --> 01:01:52,839
- I gotta go to San Francisco

1046
01:01:53,013 --> 01:01:56,582
and assure my people we're
taking care of business here.

1047
01:01:56,756 --> 01:01:59,933
- Cody!
- Just make it go away, arliss.

1048
01:02:03,328 --> 01:02:04,808
- Yeah, I'll be there in 20!

1049
01:02:04,982 --> 01:02:07,071
- You have a good lunch, Glenda.
- All right.

1050
01:02:07,245 --> 01:02:08,768
- Make sure that envelope
gets mailed for me.

1051
01:02:08,942 --> 01:02:10,291
- I will.

1052
01:02:14,426 --> 01:02:16,471
- Hey.
- Hey.

1053
01:02:16,645 --> 01:02:18,604
- The diner makes
the best lemonade around.

1054
01:02:18,778 --> 01:02:21,476
My treat?
- Sure.

1055
01:02:22,782 --> 01:02:24,784
- I was out of line
the other night,

1056
01:02:24,958 --> 01:02:27,439
and I wanted to apologize.

1057
01:02:27,613 --> 01:02:30,485
- I ought to be
apologizing.

1058
01:02:30,659 --> 01:02:32,183
- No, you're her dad,

1059
01:02:32,357 --> 01:02:33,837
and I should respect
your decision.

1060
01:02:34,011 --> 01:02:35,621
- I thought a lot
about what you said.

1061
01:02:35,795 --> 01:02:36,970
I don't want to
break her spirit.

1062
01:02:38,798 --> 01:02:39,973
Why else do you think
I let her

1063
01:02:40,147 --> 01:02:41,496
keep going back
to your place?

1064
01:02:41,670 --> 01:02:43,281
- You knew.
- Hey, I'm the sheriff.

1065
01:02:43,455 --> 01:02:44,586
- Yeah.
[Laughs]

1066
01:02:46,937 --> 01:02:48,547
Well, the wolves are ready
to be released.

1067
01:02:48,721 --> 01:02:51,680
Could I borrow Hank tomorrow?
- Sure.

1068
01:02:51,855 --> 01:02:54,118
- Just so you know,
Madison's fine with it.

1069
01:02:54,292 --> 01:02:55,423
- Good.

1070
01:02:57,425 --> 01:03:00,472
Well, I've got to get back
to work.

1071
01:03:00,646 --> 01:03:02,169
Thanks for the lemonade.

1072
01:03:05,433 --> 01:03:06,739
- Hey.

1073
01:03:06,913 --> 01:03:11,439
Everything is ok
between us?

1074
01:03:11,613 --> 01:03:15,226
- I think so.
Yeah.

1075
01:03:15,400 --> 01:03:17,271
- Ok. Good.

1076
01:03:17,445 --> 01:03:20,492
- Good.

1077
01:03:20,666 --> 01:03:24,148
- Everything's going to be
all right.

1078
01:03:24,322 --> 01:03:28,108
You're a sign, Lucinda.
A blessing.

1079
01:03:28,282 --> 01:03:32,678
And the wolves are just...
they belong in the mountains.

1080
01:03:32,852 --> 01:03:35,812
They're wild.

1081
01:03:35,986 --> 01:03:37,901
And they're just
going home tomorrow.

1082
01:03:38,075 --> 01:03:39,598
Everything's going to be
all right,

1083
01:03:39,772 --> 01:03:41,034
and I'm not going to cry.

1084
01:03:41,208 --> 01:03:44,603
[Horse snorts]
Yeah, I promised myself.

1085
01:03:50,914 --> 01:03:54,308
- How are those wolf pups doing?

1086
01:03:54,482 --> 01:03:57,398
- You mad at me?

1087
01:03:57,572 --> 01:04:00,749
- [Sighs]
How could I be mad at you?

1088
01:04:00,924 --> 01:04:05,189
- [Crying]

1089
01:04:05,363 --> 01:04:09,454
[Sniffs]
I'm so glad we came here.

1090
01:04:09,628 --> 01:04:12,326
I am.

1091
01:04:12,500 --> 01:04:15,329
And I'm ok about
the wolves leaving.

1092
01:04:15,503 --> 01:04:19,943
I just... I just
have to cry about it.

1093
01:04:20,117 --> 01:04:22,293
And that's ok, right?
- It's ok.

1094
01:04:22,467 --> 01:04:27,515
- [Sniffling]

1095
01:04:27,689 --> 01:04:28,647
Dad?

1096
01:04:28,821 --> 01:04:30,779
When you... when you cry,

1097
01:04:30,954 --> 01:04:33,173
will you let me hold you
like this?

1098
01:04:33,347 --> 01:04:35,959
I just...

1099
01:04:36,133 --> 01:04:38,439
I just think that if
you let me hold you

1100
01:04:38,613 --> 01:04:41,878
that it won't hurt so much.

1101
01:04:45,533 --> 01:04:48,362
- [Sighs]

1102
01:04:48,536 --> 01:04:49,755
- Do you remember when
Gus carved that?

1103
01:04:49,929 --> 01:04:52,236
- Hmm. Yep.

1104
01:04:52,410 --> 01:04:56,631
After he was thrown by
that big old bay stallion.

1105
01:04:56,805 --> 01:04:59,547
- [Sighs] Broke his hip,
got right back on.

1106
01:04:59,721 --> 01:05:01,593
- Never let anyone
forget it either.

1107
01:05:01,767 --> 01:05:05,466
- [Laughs]
That's how legends are made.

1108
01:05:05,640 --> 01:05:07,686
- You remember how many people
he threatened

1109
01:05:07,860 --> 01:05:08,948
to hit over the head
with this thing?

1110
01:05:09,122 --> 01:05:11,908
- Oh, over 100.
- Yeah.

1111
01:05:12,082 --> 01:05:15,346
That's what legends
are made of.

1112
01:05:18,784 --> 01:05:20,568
He looks it, doesn't he?

1113
01:05:20,742 --> 01:05:23,615
Handsome devil.

1114
01:05:23,789 --> 01:05:25,965
- You know, Bob,

1115
01:05:26,139 --> 01:05:31,797
taking on his legacy
is not a bad thing.

1116
01:05:34,452 --> 01:05:37,846
- Maybe not.

1117
01:05:38,021 --> 01:05:39,848
- Hey, they're going to
have corn beef and cabbage.

1118
01:05:40,023 --> 01:05:42,634
$2.50, and it's good!
I'm going to see you there.

1119
01:05:42,808 --> 01:05:44,723
[Laughs]
- Morning, arliss.

1120
01:05:47,682 --> 01:05:49,162
- Morning.

1121
01:05:51,817 --> 01:05:53,384
- You know, this belongs
to your son-in-law.

1122
01:05:53,558 --> 01:05:54,689
- It does?

1123
01:05:54,863 --> 01:05:57,866
- Arson's a serious crime.

1124
01:05:58,041 --> 01:05:59,738
- Oh, see, I don't know
anything about that.

1125
01:05:59,912 --> 01:06:00,782
- What about silver?

1126
01:06:00,957 --> 01:06:02,741
- Silver?

1127
01:06:02,915 --> 01:06:06,049
- Dry drilling,
killing some horses.

1128
01:06:06,223 --> 01:06:08,573
- I don't know anything
about that.

1129
01:06:08,747 --> 01:06:09,530
- I wonder if Cody does.

1130
01:06:09,704 --> 01:06:11,010
Where is he?

1131
01:06:11,184 --> 01:06:13,447
- [Laughs]
Bobby, I have no idea.

1132
01:06:13,621 --> 01:06:15,319
- [Laughs]

1133
01:06:15,493 --> 01:06:17,321
You know, arliss,
for a politician

1134
01:06:17,495 --> 01:06:18,713
you're not a very good liar.

1135
01:06:18,887 --> 01:06:20,715
- Well, he left town
yesterday.

1136
01:06:20,889 --> 01:06:22,152
- Well, that's all right.

1137
01:06:22,326 --> 01:06:23,718
I'll arrest him
when he gets back.

1138
01:06:23,892 --> 01:06:25,590
Him and anybody else
who's involved.

1139
01:06:25,764 --> 01:06:27,592
I'll see ya.

1140
01:06:27,766 --> 01:06:29,637
- I'll see ya.

1141
01:06:29,811 --> 01:06:34,860
[Dialing beeps]

1142
01:06:35,034 --> 01:06:37,558
- Yeah?
- Cody. It's arliss.

1143
01:06:37,732 --> 01:06:39,647
- Yeah, arliss, what is it?
- You just shut up and listen.

1144
01:06:39,821 --> 01:06:41,301
- What? What do you want?

1145
01:06:41,475 --> 01:06:43,521
- When you come back,
don't go into town.

1146
01:06:43,695 --> 01:06:44,957
- Ok, where then?

1147
01:06:45,131 --> 01:06:46,698
- Meet me... meet me at the mine.
- Where?

1148
01:06:46,872 --> 01:06:48,656
- The mine.
- All right.

1149
01:06:48,830 --> 01:06:50,832
- Ok.
[Hangs up]

1150
01:07:06,500 --> 01:07:08,459
- Why don't you guys
put them down over there.

1151
01:07:12,680 --> 01:07:16,684
- Bye, Indiana.
[Kissing sounds]

1152
01:07:33,614 --> 01:07:36,052
- Ok, I need you guys
to come back around here.

1153
01:07:48,760 --> 01:07:49,891
- Hey, mama.

1154
01:07:50,066 --> 01:07:52,981
[Whines]

1155
01:07:53,156 --> 01:07:54,722
It's ok.

1156
01:07:54,896 --> 01:07:58,509
- You ready?
- Yeah.

1157
01:08:01,033 --> 01:08:02,774
- Ok. Let her go.

1158
01:08:02,948 --> 01:08:04,863
[Cage door unlatching]

1159
01:08:15,091 --> 01:08:16,092
- [Sighs]

1160
01:08:17,789 --> 01:08:19,921
[Growling and yipping]

1161
01:08:22,881 --> 01:08:25,013
- Emily, um...

1162
01:08:25,188 --> 01:08:27,755
I think I just want to
walk back down on my own

1163
01:08:27,929 --> 01:08:29,105
if that's ok with you guys.

1164
01:08:29,279 --> 01:08:31,107
- Why don't you take Tim
with you.

1165
01:08:41,595 --> 01:08:43,423
[Door shuts]

1166
01:09:06,316 --> 01:09:07,882
[Birds tweeting]

1167
01:09:17,936 --> 01:09:19,459
- Hey, Madison?

1168
01:09:19,633 --> 01:09:21,374
- Yeah?

1169
01:09:21,548 --> 01:09:24,203
- You just haven't said anything
for, like, half an hour.

1170
01:09:24,377 --> 01:09:27,859
- I know.
Pretty neat, huh?

1171
01:09:28,033 --> 01:09:29,687
- Can I say something?

1172
01:09:29,861 --> 01:09:30,818
- Yeah.
- Would you hold up?

1173
01:09:30,992 --> 01:09:33,604
- Yeah.

1174
01:09:34,996 --> 01:09:36,694
[Kissing sound]

1175
01:09:36,868 --> 01:09:39,175
- Well, I said it.

1176
01:09:40,350 --> 01:09:43,179
- [Giggles]

1177
01:09:46,921 --> 01:09:49,750
[Panting]

1178
01:09:52,275 --> 01:09:54,842
- Welcome to dry gulch canyon.

1179
01:09:55,016 --> 01:09:56,931
- Dry gulch canyon?

1180
01:09:57,105 --> 01:10:00,631
- Yeah, it's just a name.

1181
01:10:00,805 --> 01:10:02,110
- What's that?

1182
01:10:02,285 --> 01:10:05,070
- Oh, that's an abandoned
silver mine.

1183
01:10:10,249 --> 01:10:13,731
Hey, what are you doing?

1184
01:10:13,905 --> 01:10:15,994
- We're going in.
- No, we're not.

1185
01:10:16,168 --> 01:10:17,952
It's a crime.
No trespassing.

1186
01:10:18,126 --> 01:10:20,390
- No, it's curiosity.

1187
01:10:20,564 --> 01:10:23,567
- Madison, this definitely
is not a good idea.

1188
01:10:23,741 --> 01:10:25,308
- Look, I just want to sneak
a peek, all right, that's all.

1189
01:10:25,482 --> 01:10:27,092
I just... you know, think of it
as an adventure.

1190
01:10:27,266 --> 01:10:28,615
- You're going to get us
arrested.

1191
01:10:28,789 --> 01:10:30,226
- My dad's the sheriff.
- Right, yes.

1192
01:10:30,400 --> 01:10:31,270
That makes it ok.
I forgot.

1193
01:10:31,444 --> 01:10:33,011
- [Laughs]

1194
01:10:36,101 --> 01:10:37,798
- Hey, you know, this could
be dangerous.

1195
01:10:37,972 --> 01:10:39,409
This mine's been closed
for years.

1196
01:10:39,583 --> 01:10:41,541
- Stop being so logical.
We're going to have fun.

1197
01:11:01,866 --> 01:11:03,041
[Squeaks]

1198
01:11:06,218 --> 01:11:09,352
- Hillridge land development,
inc.

1199
01:11:09,526 --> 01:11:12,050
- That's the company that's
building the mall in town.

1200
01:11:12,224 --> 01:11:16,707
- Yeah, I know.
But why is all their stuff here?

1201
01:12:13,067 --> 01:12:14,112
[Squeaks]

1202
01:12:32,043 --> 01:12:34,393
- Cody. Cody, is that you?

1203
01:12:34,567 --> 01:12:35,960
- Who did you think it was?

1204
01:12:36,134 --> 01:12:39,006
- What happened?

1205
01:12:39,180 --> 01:12:40,965
- Business.
- Business?

1206
01:12:41,139 --> 01:12:42,923
- Mm-hmm.

1207
01:12:45,535 --> 01:12:48,189
[Sighs]
The hillridge boys...

1208
01:12:48,364 --> 01:12:50,104
Are not very happy.

1209
01:12:50,278 --> 01:12:51,584
- Yeah, well, neither am I.

1210
01:12:51,758 --> 01:12:54,282
You're sloppy,
and you're impatient.

1211
01:12:54,457 --> 01:12:57,373
The last time you were here,
you forgot to lock that gate.

1212
01:13:07,600 --> 01:13:09,689
- Well...

1213
01:13:09,863 --> 01:13:13,127
You think I'm impatient?

1214
01:13:13,301 --> 01:13:17,480
You don't want to meet
the boys from San Francisco.

1215
01:13:17,654 --> 01:13:19,395
They'll do more than
give you a black eye.

1216
01:13:22,615 --> 01:13:25,313
They'll slit your throat
or get me to do it.

1217
01:13:25,488 --> 01:13:27,054
[Laughs]

1218
01:13:27,228 --> 01:13:29,405
- Did you kill those horses?

1219
01:13:29,579 --> 01:13:30,841
- What if I did?

1220
01:13:31,015 --> 01:13:32,538
- See, I didn't agree to that.

1221
01:13:32,712 --> 01:13:34,192
And I didn't agree to arson
either.

1222
01:13:34,366 --> 01:13:38,152
- You think you're
running this show?

1223
01:13:38,326 --> 01:13:42,113
Now, I prefer action.

1224
01:13:42,287 --> 01:13:44,942
Like tonight.

1225
01:13:45,116 --> 01:13:47,205
- Tonight?
What do you mean?

1226
01:13:47,379 --> 01:13:53,167
- Mmm. As of tonight,
it's bye-bye horses.

1227
01:13:53,341 --> 01:13:54,691
Got me some poison.
It's out in the truck.

1228
01:13:54,865 --> 01:13:56,519
- Oh, no, no.
See, you can't do that.

1229
01:13:56,693 --> 01:13:58,042
Those horses are protected.
Listen...

1230
01:13:58,216 --> 01:13:59,347
[slapping]

1231
01:13:59,522 --> 01:14:01,915
[Thudding]

1232
01:14:02,089 --> 01:14:06,790
- Now, with those horses gone,
it's bye-bye Bobby.

1233
01:14:06,964 --> 01:14:09,401
We'll be strip mining
in no time.

1234
01:14:09,575 --> 01:14:12,970
Welcome to the new town
of hope

1235
01:14:13,144 --> 01:14:16,103
where there is always hope.
[Laughs]

1236
01:14:16,277 --> 01:14:17,235
- The sheriff said
he's going to arrest you.

1237
01:14:17,409 --> 01:14:19,280
- Not if he can't find me.

1238
01:14:19,455 --> 01:14:22,501
As for my sweet little Emily,

1239
01:14:22,675 --> 01:14:25,156
if her barn burns down tonight,

1240
01:14:25,330 --> 01:14:29,029
I don't figure she'll
refuse my next offer.

1241
01:14:29,203 --> 01:14:30,509
She can't afford it.

1242
01:14:30,683 --> 01:14:32,555
Toast, arliss.

1243
01:14:32,729 --> 01:14:36,297
To this town's two silver mining
millionaires!

1244
01:14:36,472 --> 01:14:37,821
- I don't want any part of this!

1245
01:14:37,995 --> 01:14:39,518
- But you are part of it,
old man.

1246
01:14:39,692 --> 01:14:41,433
- I did not commit any crime.

1247
01:14:41,607 --> 01:14:44,088
- Guilt by association,
arliss?

1248
01:14:44,262 --> 01:14:46,090
Have a drink.
- I...

1249
01:14:46,264 --> 01:14:48,135
- go on.
[Laughs]

1250
01:14:48,309 --> 01:14:49,441
Keep your mouth shut,

1251
01:14:49,615 --> 01:14:51,922
or am I going to have to
kill you?

1252
01:14:52,096 --> 01:14:53,837
[Blade clicks]

1253
01:14:57,493 --> 01:14:59,146
- [Screams]
[Thuds]

1254
01:15:06,327 --> 01:15:08,504
- [Sighs]
What have we got here?

1255
01:15:11,419 --> 01:15:13,770
Well...the young miss hart.

1256
01:15:13,944 --> 01:15:22,039
â™ª

1257
01:15:27,348 --> 01:15:29,960
[Car door bell]

1258
01:15:30,134 --> 01:15:33,529
- Hey.
- Hey.

1259
01:15:33,703 --> 01:15:37,968
- So, Madison do ok
saying goodbye to those pups?

1260
01:15:38,142 --> 01:15:40,187
- Yeah. I think she surprised
all of us.

1261
01:15:40,361 --> 01:15:42,450
- Great.

1262
01:15:42,625 --> 01:15:44,365
Well, I just thought I'd come by
and pick her up,

1263
01:15:44,540 --> 01:15:45,976
see if she was ok.

1264
01:15:46,150 --> 01:15:48,021
- Oh, well, she's not...
she's not here.

1265
01:15:48,195 --> 01:15:51,416
- No? She's not at the house.
I just talked to Hank.

1266
01:15:51,590 --> 01:15:52,548
He figured she was
on her way here.

1267
01:15:52,722 --> 01:15:54,158
- Well, maybe she's on her way.

1268
01:15:54,332 --> 01:15:57,335
- Maybe.

1269
01:15:57,509 --> 01:16:00,468
Maybe I'll wait.

1270
01:16:00,643 --> 01:16:02,601
If that's all right with you.

1271
01:16:02,775 --> 01:16:03,776
- Sure.

1272
01:16:11,479 --> 01:16:16,659
- Sheriff! Hank! Hank! Hank!

1273
01:16:16,833 --> 01:16:20,053
Madison, she's in trouble.
- Madison?

1274
01:16:20,227 --> 01:16:22,969
Hang on a second.
I've got to call Bob.

1275
01:16:24,536 --> 01:16:25,885
- Come on inside.

1276
01:16:26,059 --> 01:16:27,234
I'll get you something
cold to drink.

1277
01:16:27,408 --> 01:16:31,108
[Cell phone ringing]

1278
01:16:31,282 --> 01:16:32,631
- Yeah, this is Bob.

1279
01:16:32,805 --> 01:16:34,285
- Bob, Madison's in trouble.

1280
01:16:34,459 --> 01:16:36,243
You better get over here
right now.

1281
01:16:41,422 --> 01:16:44,425
- Hello, sunshine.

1282
01:16:44,600 --> 01:16:47,385
- [Whimpers]

1283
01:16:47,559 --> 01:16:50,518
- [Sighs]
You're all by yourself here?

1284
01:16:50,693 --> 01:16:53,173
- Listen, Madison,
whatever you heard...

1285
01:16:53,347 --> 01:16:56,568
- arliss! Quiet.

1286
01:16:56,742 --> 01:16:59,005
- I just wanted progress
for our town.

1287
01:16:59,179 --> 01:17:02,095
And to make a little money.
Is that so awful?

1288
01:17:02,269 --> 01:17:03,749
I didn't do any of
those bad things.

1289
01:17:03,923 --> 01:17:06,056
You've got to know that.
I mean, I'm the mayor.

1290
01:17:06,230 --> 01:17:08,232
- Not for long.

1291
01:17:10,147 --> 01:17:11,278
- So...

1292
01:17:13,890 --> 01:17:15,631
You going to keep quiet
about this?

1293
01:17:15,805 --> 01:17:19,504
- You're history, Cody.

1294
01:17:19,678 --> 01:17:23,247
- You got spunk
like your grandpa.

1295
01:17:23,421 --> 01:17:26,729
Only thing is...

1296
01:17:26,903 --> 01:17:32,517
If you disappear,
then who's history?

1297
01:17:32,691 --> 01:17:34,606
- You can't hurt this girl.
- Shut up!

1298
01:17:34,780 --> 01:17:36,477
She can sink us.
Is that what you want?

1299
01:17:36,652 --> 01:17:38,523
- No, but...
- but what?

1300
01:17:38,697 --> 01:17:41,308
We have worked too hard
for this.

1301
01:17:41,482 --> 01:17:42,701
I have worked too hard
for this.

1302
01:17:42,875 --> 01:17:45,008
Nobody's getting in my way.

1303
01:17:53,886 --> 01:17:56,628
[Snarls]

1304
01:17:58,456 --> 01:18:00,676
[Growling]

1305
01:18:01,459 --> 01:18:03,287
- Oh...

1306
01:18:03,461 --> 01:18:07,291
[Wolf snarls]

1307
01:18:07,465 --> 01:18:11,121
- Shh, shh, shh.

1308
01:18:11,295 --> 01:18:13,166
[Snarling]

1309
01:18:13,340 --> 01:18:15,429
Shh.

1310
01:18:17,518 --> 01:18:19,042
[Wolf growls]

1311
01:18:27,572 --> 01:18:29,705
- Hank, you come with me.

1312
01:18:29,879 --> 01:18:32,098
Emily, Tim, stay by the truck.

1313
01:18:32,272 --> 01:18:34,057
[Sighs]

1314
01:18:54,381 --> 01:18:57,994
[Wolf growling]

1315
01:18:58,168 --> 01:19:01,345
- Dad?

1316
01:19:01,519 --> 01:19:03,390
Move very slowly.

1317
01:19:05,479 --> 01:19:08,526
[Snarling]

1318
01:19:10,397 --> 01:19:13,226
Trust me.

1319
01:19:13,400 --> 01:19:16,099
- Hank...

1320
01:19:20,059 --> 01:19:24,281
- Ok. Now walk towards me
very slowly.

1321
01:19:24,455 --> 01:19:25,848
Dakota, this is my dad,

1322
01:19:26,022 --> 01:19:29,199
the most important person
in my life.

1323
01:19:29,373 --> 01:19:31,549
[Wolf whimpers]

1324
01:19:31,723 --> 01:19:33,203
He's not going to hurt us.
He's going to help us.

1325
01:19:33,377 --> 01:19:34,465
He's just going to
untie me, ok?

1326
01:19:34,639 --> 01:19:36,772
Talk to her.

1327
01:19:38,599 --> 01:19:40,340
- Hey, Dakota.

1328
01:19:43,604 --> 01:19:48,479
I can see you've been taking
good care of my daughter,

1329
01:19:48,653 --> 01:19:51,351
and I'm grateful for that.

1330
01:19:52,875 --> 01:19:55,312
And I want to thank you
for looking after her.

1331
01:19:57,444 --> 01:19:59,229
I'll take over now

1332
01:19:59,403 --> 01:20:02,449
if that's all right with you.

1333
01:20:02,623 --> 01:20:05,235
[Sniffs and snarls]

1334
01:20:08,455 --> 01:20:10,501
[Whimpers]

1335
01:20:10,675 --> 01:20:12,459
- Thank you, Dakota.

1336
01:20:12,633 --> 01:20:14,461
Give your babies
kisses for me, ok?

1337
01:20:17,595 --> 01:20:20,337
- Cody, arliss,

1338
01:20:20,511 --> 01:20:21,904
you boys are under arrest.

1339
01:20:22,078 --> 01:20:23,470
You have the right
to remain silent...

1340
01:20:23,644 --> 01:20:24,471
- [spits]
- [Punch]

1341
01:20:24,645 --> 01:20:27,257
- [Groans]

1342
01:20:27,431 --> 01:20:28,606
- You have the right to
an attorney

1343
01:20:28,780 --> 01:20:29,999
before answering any questions.

1344
01:20:30,173 --> 01:20:31,696
If you cannot afford
an attorney,

1345
01:20:31,870 --> 01:20:32,610
one will be appointed for you
by the court.

1346
01:20:34,525 --> 01:20:36,832
Ok, let's go.

1347
01:20:43,403 --> 01:20:45,579
- So what am I going to do
when summer's over

1348
01:20:45,753 --> 01:20:47,581
and you go back to Fresno?

1349
01:20:47,755 --> 01:20:50,367
- There's email.
- And...?

1350
01:20:50,541 --> 01:20:51,759
- And telephones.

1351
01:20:51,934 --> 01:20:53,457
- And...

1352
01:20:53,631 --> 01:20:56,199
- And weekends.

1353
01:20:56,373 --> 01:20:59,767
Bus leaves every Friday
right after school.

1354
01:20:59,942 --> 01:21:02,205
- Friday, not Saturday.
Right?

1355
01:21:02,379 --> 01:21:04,424
- Right.

1356
01:21:04,598 --> 01:21:06,600
- Hey...

1357
01:21:06,774 --> 01:21:10,517
You know, I want to be
a doctor, too.

1358
01:21:10,691 --> 01:21:13,172
- What kind?
- What do you think?

1359
01:21:14,957 --> 01:21:17,742
[Horse neighs and snorts]

1360
01:21:28,057 --> 01:21:31,364
- So is there anything else
I've got to apologize for?

1361
01:21:31,538 --> 01:21:33,105
- No.

1362
01:21:33,279 --> 01:21:35,542
- Good.

1363
01:21:35,716 --> 01:21:37,370
How about you?

1364
01:21:37,544 --> 01:21:39,503
Anything else you've got to
apologize for?

1365
01:21:39,677 --> 01:21:41,070
- No.

1366
01:21:41,244 --> 01:21:44,247
- Oh, I'm glad we got
that settled.

1367
01:21:57,042 --> 01:21:58,870
- You think they make
a cute couple?

1368
01:21:59,044 --> 01:22:00,567
- I think they make
a great couple.

1369
01:22:03,875 --> 01:22:04,963
- So do we.

1370
01:22:05,137 --> 01:22:07,400
- Race you.
- You're on.

1371
01:22:07,574 --> 01:22:09,402
- Ya!
- Ha!

1372
01:22:09,576 --> 01:22:11,665
[Horses whinny]

